{"title_page": "The Big Night In", "text_new": "{{distinguish|The Big Night In with John Foreman}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| italic_title             = y\n| name                     = The Big Night In\n| image                    = The Big Night In logo.jpg\n| image_upright            = \n| image_size               = 250\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Telethon]]\n| creator                  = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Children in Need]] \n* [[Comic Relief]]\n}}\n| developer                = \n| director                 = \n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list -->\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[United Kingdom]]\n| executive_producer       = Peter Davey\n| producer                 = Peter Davey\n| editor                   = <!-- Film editors -->\n| camera                   = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime                  = {{Duration|h=3}}\n| company                  = <!-- Production companies only -->\n| distributor              = \n| budget                   = \n| network                  = \n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|04|23|df=y}}\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations -->\n| website                  = https://www.bbc.co.uk/bignightin\n| production_website       = <!-- use |production_website_title= to change the display title. -->\n}}\n'''''The Big Night In''''' is a United Kingdom [[telethon]] being broadcast by [[BBC television]] from 7pm to 10pm on 23 April 2020,<ref name=\"Metro-12558735\">{{cite news |title=When is The Big Night In on TV and who is taking part in the BBC One show? |url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/04/15/big-night-tv-taking-part-bbc-one-show-12558735/ |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=Metro |date=15 April 2020 }}</ref> to support those affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\"Metro-12521241\">{{cite web |title=Children In Need and Comic Relief join forces for first time for coronavirus |url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/04/07/children-need-comic-relief-join-forces-first-time-coronavirus-relief-12521241/ |website=Metro |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=7 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Independent-a9474766\">{{cite news |title=BBC Big Night In: Peter Kay, Little Britain and Vicar of Dibley to return for special charity event - follow live |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/bbc-big-night-in-live-stream-channel-best-bits-peter-kay-little-britain-catch-up-watch-a9474766.html |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=The Independent |date=23 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> The British government will match all public donations, with a minimum of \u00a320 million.<ref name=\"BBC-52379802\">{{cite web |title=Doctor Who stars unite for BBC's Big Night In |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-52379802 |website=BBC News |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt is the first joint initiative between two BBC telethon charities, [[Children in Need]] and [[Comic Relief]].<ref name=\"Metro-12521241\" /> The [[showrunner]] and [[executive producer]] for the BBC is Peter Davey.<ref name=\"YLG2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/leisure/showbiz/18400491.foo-fighters-praise-live-lounge-charity-cover-ahead-bbcs-big-night/|title=Foo Fighters praise Live Lounge charity cover ahead of BBC\u2019s Big Night In|work=Your Local Guardian|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Presenters and performers ==\nThe presenters include [[Lenny Henry]], [[Matt Baker]] and [[Davina McCall]], with [[Zoe Ball]] and [[Paddy McGuinness]] scheduled to appear later.<ref name=\"Metro-12558735\" />  The studio presenters will maintain [[social distancing]], while most of those appearing will take part remotely, via [[Videotelephony|video links]].<ref name=\"Independent-a9474766\" /> There will be comedy appearances by [[Steve Coogan]], [[Rob Brydon]], [[Jack Whitehall]], [[Romesh Ranganathan]], and [[Miranda Hart]],<ref name=\"BBC-52379802\" /> as well as solo music performances from [[Sam Smith]] and [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/bignightin/theshow|title=Big Night In: The Show|website=BBC|url-status=live|access-date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Line-up ==\n\nExcluding appearances from guests including [[Mary Berry]] and [[Little Mix]], [[BBC]]'s advertised line-up is as follows:<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"Metro-12558735\" /><ref name=\"ES-LB\">{{cite web |title=Little Britain to return to TV for Big Night In charity telethon |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/stayingin/tvfilm/little-britain-comeback-big-night-in-bbc-a4416191.html |website=Evening Standard |accessdate=23 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC-52379802\" /><ref name=\"Beaumont-Thomas\">{{cite news |last1=Beaumont-Thomas |first1=Ben |title=BBC Radio 1 launches coronavirus charity song with Dua Lipa, Chris Martin and more |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/apr/20/bbc-radio-1-launches-coronavirus-charity-song-with-dua-lipa-chris-martin-and-more |accessdate=23 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Miranda Hart]] and the cast of ''[[Miranda (TV series)|Miranda]].''\n* [[Sam Smith]] performed \"[[Lay Me Down (Sam Smith song)|Lay Me Down]]\"\n* A lockdown sermon by ''[[The Vicar of Dibley]]'' featuring [[Dawn French]]\n* Premiere of the video for [[Live Lounge Allstars]]' [[Times Like These (Live Lounge Allstars charity single)|cover version]] of Foo Fighter's \"Times Like These\"\n* [[Steve Coogan]] and [[Rob Brydon]] in ''[[The Trip (2010 TV series)|The Trip]]''\n* [[Catherine Tate]] and [[David Tennant]] perform: \"[[Lauren Cooper|Lauren]] the \u2018[[Am I bovvered|Am I Bovvered]]\u2019 teenager gets home-schooled\"\n* [[Matt Lucas]] and the [[BBC Orchestras and Singers|BBC Orchestra]] perform \"Baked Potato Song\"\n* [[Celeste (singer)|Celeste]] performs a cover of Bill Withers' \"[[Lean on Me (song)|Lean On Me]]\"\n* [[Jack Whitehall]] in [[Bad Education (TV series)|''Bad Education'']] with [[Mathew Horne|Matthew Horne]] and [[Anthony Joshua]]\n* ''[[People Just Do Nothing]]''{{Clarify|date=April 2020}}\n* [[EastEnders]] pub quiz in the [[Queen Vic Fire Week|Queen Vic]] hosted by [[Ian Beale]]\n* [[Peter Kay]] and the British public remake the \"[[(Is This the Way to) Amarillo|Is This the Way to Amarillo]]\" video\n* The first televisual ''[[Little Britain]]'' sketch for over a decade\n* [[Tess Daly]] and [[Claudia Winkleman]] host a ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'' choreography challenge\n* [[Romesh Ranganathan]]'s Isolation Diary\n* [[Joe Wicks (coach)|Joe Wicks]]' exercise secrets\n* A reunion of actors who have played the title role in [[Doctor Who]] salute [[National Health Service|NHS]] health workers\n* Stand-up at home from [[Jason Manford]], [[Rosie Jones (comedian)|Rosie Jones]], [[Tez Ilyas]], [[Dane Baptiste]], [[Russell Kane]], The Lost Voice Guy, [[Nish Kumar]] and more\n* [[Liam Payne]], [[Olly Murs]], [[Leona Lewis]], [[Nicole Scherzinger]], [[Freya Ridings]], [[Katherine Jenkins]], [[Alfie Boe]], [[Gregory Porter]] and more join [[Gary Barlow]] to perform \"[[Sing (Gary Barlow song)|Sing]]\"\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n*{{Official website}}\n*{{BBC programme}}\n*{{IMDb title|tt12183158}}\n<!--\n{{Children in Need}}\n{{Comic Relief}} please wait until after broadcast, so we can make best use of 'what links here' -->\n\n[[Category:Telethons]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Children in Need]]\n[[Category:Comic Relief]]\n[[Category:BBC Television programmes]]\n[[Category:British telethons]]\n[[Category:2020 in British television]]\n[[Category:2020 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2020 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Charity events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|The Big Night In with John Foreman}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| italic_title             = y\n| name                     = The Big Night In\n| image                    = The Big Night In logo.jpg\n| image_upright            = \n| image_size               = 250\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Telethon]]\n| creator                  = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Children in Need]] \n* [[Comic Relief]]\n}}\n| developer                = \n| director                 = \n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = <!-- Organized by broadcast credit order, with new main cast added to the end of the list -->\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[United Kingdom]]\n| executive_producer       = Peter Davey\n| producer                 = Peter Davey\n| editor                   = <!-- Film editors -->\n| camera                   = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime                  = {{Duration|h=3}}\n| company                  = <!-- Production companies only -->\n| distributor              = \n| budget                   = \n| network                  = \n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|04|23|df=y}}\n| related  